# Projeto: core-system

## O que é

Biblioteca compartilhada usada como git submodule por projetos pessoais. Fornece autenticação, gerenciamento de arquivos, infraestrutura e componentes UI reutilizáveis.

## Estrutura

```
core-system/
├── backend/
│   └── src/
│       ├── Core.Common/          # BaseEntity, Result<T>, extensions
│       ├── Core.Auth/            # Session auth, RBAC, rate limiting
│       ├── Core.FileManagement/  # Upload, storage, deduplication
│       └── Core.Infrastructure/  # EF Core + MySQL (Pomelo)
├── frontend/
│   ├── components/ui/            # shadcn/ui components
│   ├── contexts/                 # CoreAuthProvider
│   ├── hooks/                    # use-toast, use-debounce, use-mobile
│   ├── lib/                      # api-client, format, storage, utils
│   └── types/
└── cursor-rules/                 # Rule templates for consuming projects
```

## Regras Específicas do Core

- This is a **library**, not a standalone app -- no `Program.cs`, no `appsettings.json`, no `.env` here
- Configuration is provided by consuming projects via extension methods (`AddCoreAuth()`, `AddCoreInfrastructure()`)
- All public APIs must be well-documented with XML comments (backend) since consuming projects depend on them
- Breaking changes to public interfaces require careful consideration
- Frontend exports via `@core/*` path alias -- keep import paths stable
- `cursor-rules/` contains templates for consuming projects; `.cursor/rules/` contains rules for this repo
- When adding new shadcn/ui components, follow the existing pattern in `frontend/components/ui/`
